e of things to note is that the style of noodle they use at Ippudo is a very thin soup noodle. It's very different from a typical alkaline egg noodle and is much tougher and doesn't absorb as much of the broth. The wheat and texture is very different. One thing I did like about Ippudo is the selection. They had various ramen styles available in all kinds of flavors and they even had a special. However you couldn't pick from different types of noodles unlike their counterpart Minca. That being said they do make a mean bowl of ramen and I left the place refreshed and very happy. The service although appearing as frantic and chaotic is very attentive and was excellent. The prices are a bit higher than what I had wished but all in all it was a solid experience. If you do intend on going there just keep in mind that the lines can be long, and in many occasions, will surpass an hour - arrive early, as close to 11AM as possible and just make it an early lunch. It will pay off. Especially since they don't take reservations there.
