oise. If you're visiting from elsewhere, you might not be ready for this. The attention paid to our glasses of sake was pretty cool. I think I was allowed to empty my glass once. Every other time, someone came by and filled it when it dipped below half. The same can be said for our water. Overall, this is a place I'd hit again, as long as I have the proper ingredients: good company and a place to go for a couple hours.
