I am updating because I want to raise my last review on Ippudo by a star! The experience just seems to get better with each and every visit. Everything from the service, atmosphere, to the food is stellar. Yes, Ippudo is always busy, but there is little to no reason to complain or be surprised by this. Is it worth the wait? It always is, and it's pain-free. They have a wonderful, organized system for waits. They take down your name and number and text you two times during your wait; 30 min and 5 min before your table is ready. In this case, you don't have to physically wait in line in the restaurant if the wait is an hour or more. There are a ton of bars and other places to check out around Astor Place though, so take advantage of that. Ippudo was rated as having one of the best ramens in the city, so it's definitely worth checking out if you love quality ramen. No, this is not the grocery store ramen. They create the ramen here like a form of art. The food tastes as good as it looks. The noodles are always al dente and the broth is succulent and rich with flavors. I have ordered the Shiromaru Hakata Classic and recently tried the Akamaru Modern. Between the two popular dishes, I prefer the Modern; the classic is more mild while the Modern has a bit of an extra kick with the added garlic oil. Both are very delicious though, and I recommend either. For a side dish, you must get the Hirata pork buns. I cannot exaggerate how awesomely delicious they are. If you like raw fish or want a cold appetizer, definitely give the Tako Wasabi a try. It's basically raw baby octopus with fresh wasabi. Overall, the food is always consistently awesome here. For the ramen, you can order 'kae-dama' which means another helping of ramen (for only $3 per order). Just make sure you save some extra broth and room in your stomach. If you waited over an hour for a table, I would definitely go for the second serving.
