autiful and happy tattooed lady, had recommended the "modern" ramen ("akamaru modern") and we also chose Karaka Men, their spicy ramen.  Granted, I'm not a ramen snob, but we were both really impressed - very pretty and very delicious!  If you like spice the Karaka Med is killer!  I ate way more than I should have because they were so good!  Frankly, these are pretty big bowls of ramen - like enough for two people.  Never mind a second helping - amazingly they offer you the option of eating all your noodles then telling your waitperson "Kaedama, please" to order another helping of noodles to be placed in the remaining broth for 2 bucks!  Another option for those with bottomless stomachs are the many toppings that can be added to any ramen bowl. Check this wonderful ramen house out if you like ramen, don't mind spending $15 for a bowl, like a lot of youth around you, like a really hearty din at your diner, don't mind waiting to join a communal table and if you want a great New York experience!
