Ippudo was one of my top restaurants to try while in New York. They're open late, so after a very long day walking around Midtown, I was glad to finally sit down at a table and enjoy a delicious, filling bowl of Japanese comfort food. We arrived around 9:30PM on a Tuesday and were seated within 10 minutes. The restaurant was dark and loud, but overall had a fun, friendly vibe to it. Service was fast and extremely attentive. We ordered and shared the Shiromaru Hakata Classic ramen and Akamaru Modern ramen. Noodles had a great texture, nice and firm. The chashu was delicious and tender, but it didn't have a very soft "melt in your mouth" texture. The classic's broth was slightly salty, but very creamy. However, I highly preferred the modern's broth because of the amazing, aromatic garlic oil! It smelled very strong that if you took a big whiff of it, you could almost taste it. On the contrary, the taste was very mild, which is still a good thing because garlic shouldn't be too powerful that it takes away other savory flavors in the broth. It was so good I finished every last drop (and I rarely finish the soup at any other ramen place). We had a little room left for dessert and decided to try the green tea brûlée and the mascarpone cheese w/ green tea ice cream. The brûlée was slightly bitter, but the crisp, burnt sugar shell and (slightly sweet) green tea ice cream complimented it really well. The mascarpone cheese was dense and great as well. It came with crushed pistachio, small dark chocolate squares, and honey drizzle. Ippudo's mild, not-overly sweet desserts pair well after eating their ramen. Normally, I don't like the idea of paying $15+ for a bowl of ramen. But splurge a little here. Flavors are great and you won't regret it! And if you get the chance, check out their cool bathroom faucet! Haha.
