er & scallions.  The ramen noodles in this dish was also excellent.  The flavor of the soup is much more milder and not as strong as the tonkotsu one, it not as salty.  But still excellent also, this would be a second choice. Note also for all the Ramen dishes, you can get a Kae-dama order for additional $2.  Which is extra noodle on a plate to add back into your ramen dish.  This is worth the extra two dollars since ramen here cost $13 per bowl.  As long as you have a decent amount of broth left it be a good option, most likely people can finish another order of noodles.
