uly a Japan delicatessen because it can go good or bad.  At Ippudo, they mastered it from drinks to sake to appetizers to the main dish, RAMEN!   The service here was also excellent but the host at the front desk seemed rude and did not enjoy her job :/.  I just ignored her attitude every time I went up to check how much longer we had to wait.   The prices here are high but then again, this is New York, everything is a little more expensive compared to California.  I am still in search of a place comparable to Ippudo in Bay Area, California.  So far, only one place comes close and I am loving it.  Ippudo, I will be back to devour your yummy RAMEN & appetizers!
