don't get me wrong, the food is good (i usually like the modern or pork buns) - but the hostess (especially the one with the crazy spirally curly hair) are so so rude.  big power trip.  i've been several times and obviously know there will be a wait.  this is what happened: she told us our wait would be 30-40 minutes (after putting our name down an hour before).  in 35 minutes we checked back and my friend and i both heard her say "your table is ready, they are just cleaning it."  i thought that was great and went to get the rest of our party that was waiting outside to come inside.  15 minutes later i go back to her and say, what happened to our table?  and she says "i SAID they were PAYING.  they are still sitting there."  whoa whoa whoa.  we both heard her say they were cleaning the table.  cleaning does not sound like paying.  she was pretty nasty and her attitude made the wait for the food totally not worth it.  they also tried to rush us out and we refused to be rushed.  how can we have our dining time be half the time of our waiting time??  especially when we see empty tables around us.  i think ippudo has a huge power trip and is not worth the wait.  they need to straighten up their attitude.
